CR (Fig.
5 i
) is symmetrical, slender, and nearly straight. The entire posterior edge is serrated and shows patches of denticles at its base. The anterior (Ga) and posterior (Gp) claws are two-serrate, with the Ga being longer. The anterior (Sa) and posterior (Sp) setae are subequally long and serrated. Sp located close to Gp.
